tip.text: Refined, delicate, ultra fresh and awesome sushi courses from Chef Shingo Takahashi. Nothing less than stellar. Approx 25,000JPY for 40 pieces menu. Absolute bomb!
The no frills restaurant here is a gem. Dishes are yummy and authentically Penang Nyonya. Penang Char Beehoon, Perut Ikan, Lobak, Ju Hu Char, Curry Fish Head, Assam Prawns & Char Kuey Teow stood out.

contact.facebookName: 中马锺灵校友会 Persatuan Alumni Chung Ling Wilayah Tengah

venue.name: Chung Ling Old Boys Association Wilayah Tengah 中馬鍾靈校友會

tip.text: Ask for the US Tomahawk Wagyu Ribeye. Perfectly grilled. The beef fats and leftover meats are used for a yummy Beef Char Kuey Teow ever! The Leng Chai Curry Hotpot is worth a try too.
Tucked away on Lrg Maarof, this cafe serves great strong robust coffee, with few "Asian" options thrown in, e.g. Viet & Gula Melaka. You can order wok fried noodles for lunch too. Worth a try.
Aussie outlet from Canberra known for their "Freakshakes". The Pretzella and Muddy Pat are excellent. Toppings are great but shake is a wee bit too thin, but still good. Cakes are superb.
New upscale outlet serving local food, that is really good with pretty ok prices. Satay, Korean Fried Chicken, Nasi Lemak are all good. Will return to try the Ayam Cheese Pot and Lobster Curry.
Clams/mussels with many varieties of preparation are the main stars. Lemon Garlic Butter, Ginger and Lemongrass, Basilik, and Tumeric Butter are standouts. You can try the Summer Salad too.
The board says it all : "Nodi" denotes the art of connecting people with coffee. And they do just that. Great robust tasting coffee, served at the correct temperature. Check it out.
Helmed by Toni Valero of Ohla Tapas, this new outfit serves creative, modern and yummy Spanish fare. Try the Iberico Pork Tartare, Grilled Octopus, Suckling Pig, and the Chilli Padi Ice Cream!
Upscale cucina by BIG. Prices are steep, but it's worth a try. Go for Capellini, Truffle Tagliatelle, Seafood Risotto, and the Braised Shortrib. For meat lovers, ask for the Ribeye on the bone too.
If you're looking for yummy caramelized char siew, crispy aromatic siew yoke, and great Hakka minced meat noodles, look no further. This is easily one of the better options available.
Seriously yummy pies here. Try the Pulled Lamb Pie and the Nacho's Pie with Cheesy Sauce. Make sure you add on the full works ie peas, mash and gravy as options. Try the Elvis or Choc Mint as finale.
Two Michelin Stars outlet that serves one of the best sushis in Tokyo. Friendly and jovial service, the chefs explains the type of fish used in each morsel. USD200 for 45 pieces of heaven. Joy!

formattedAddress: 西麻布4-1-15 (セブン西麻布 B1F)

tip.text: They have been around for a good 60 years, and they dish out excellent Nyonya Cuisine. Try the signature Fried Roast Pork with Garlic, Assam Pomfret, Mui Choy Pork, Sharks Fin Omelette & Inchi Kabin.

venue.name: Tek Sen Restaurant (Tek Sen Restaurant (德盛飯店))

tip.text: They serve seriously yummy and excellent food here. Check out Bitter Gourd Omelette, Braised Fish with Yam, Steamed Chicken, Tofu with Brinjal, and Sweet Vinegar Pork Ribs. Highly recommended.
Tuck into possibly the best Popiah in Penang. Order the ones with added crab meat. The stock served with the Popiah is just heavenly. Wash all down with coconut water or ambra juice!
Ceiling price outlet helmed by 3 Michelin Star chef Saito San. 3 courses to choose from. Uni sushi and the grilled beef option are the best. Worth the price? No. More glam over substance.
Opened by native Spaniard restauranteurs, you can't get more authentic than this. The Squid Ink Paella, garlic gambas, Spanish Omelette, pork cutlet, & tomato salad are tops. Don't forget Churros!

location.address: The Signature, 3 Jalan Sri Hartamas 22, Desa Sri Hartamas
formattedAddress: The Signature, 3 Jalan Sri Hartamas 22, Desa Sri Hartamas

contact.facebookName: Marta's Kitchen in KL Paella and Tapas

tip.text: This is arguably the best Wagyu Don in Singapore. Order the Fat Cow Donburi and Foie Gras Wagyu Don. For starters, go for the Hamachi Sashimi & black truffle paired with Japanese Tomato Salad.
This place is not rated any Michelin Stars but the dishes they churn out deserves the accolades. Excellent selection of sashimi, sushi and maki, coupled with friendly service and great ambience.

location.crossStreet: グランドハイアット東京 6F
formattedAddress: 六本木6-10-3 (グランドハイアット東京 6F)

tip.text: With one Michelin Star under its belt and blessed with good genes being part of the L'Atelier du Robuchon group, you are guaranteed an excellent Teppanyaki experience here. Try the special course.
Helmed by the former chef of Cocotei, you can expect nothing but the best Japanese spread around. Try the RM350 omakase for a display of their vast culinary expertise. You won't be disappointed.
Famed Japanese Crepe Cake from New York, now with two outlets in HK. The signature Crepe Cake with vanilla custard filling will send you to heaven. So will Checkers and the Cream Cheese Cake.
New premium outlet for steak lovers from BIG. You get a good range of quality steaks to choose from, with more than good selection of sides and mains. Prices are steep but do try.
Brewing "Comexim" coffee beans originally from Brazil, but packed in Kew, Melbourne, this place serves really great coffee. Cakes are to die for too. The aroma therapy durian and peanut butter are 👍.
Be prepared to wait for approximately one hour, but you will be rewarded with the best original Ipoh Kuey Teow, smooth poached Chicken and crunchy Taugeh. Try the Caramel Custard and Pork Satay too.
Great fine dining Chinese Vegetarian Dishes. Try the Satay Skewers with Water Chestnuts and Mushrooms, the Spinach Soup, the Signature Tofu, and the Premium Soy Fried Noodle.
The food, the ambience and even the servers scream "Authentic Thai" here. Try the Bangkok Nam Tok Noodles, Laab Gai Salad, Haatyai Fried Chicken, Ice Blended Coconut. Pad Thai is a tad too sweet.
SGD400++ for 10 of the choicest, freshest seafood and meat dishes, all expertly crafted and to die for in tastes, at one of the Top 50 restaurants in the world. Expensive? Yes. Worth it? Definitely!

formattedAddress: L2-01 The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands (10 Bayfront Ave)
location.address: L2-01 The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands

tip.text: You have only 4 lobster dishes on the menu and all of them are very well executed with 600g of lobster each at RM158 per pop. Try all of them if possible. Just wished they serve more noodles though..
Food is excellent here. The best way to sample an array of dishes is to try one of the 3 options of Degustation Menu. Try US Prime Short Rib, Roasted Black Cod & Seared Foie Gras. Go for Menu 4.
Great restaurant helmed by Brent Savage, the Australian Chef of The Year 2015. Start with Pork Cheek or Spot Prawn Cocktail, to mains of Oyster Blade Fillet or Red Mulloway, lastly Violet Ice Cream.
One of the Top 30 restaurants in the world, you get innovative (even jaw dropping) dishes and to die for views! Mud Crab Congee, Black lip Abalone & Wagyu excel. Don't leave w/o trying the Snow Egg!!
Excellent sushi, sashimi and Robata dishes in a buzzy, cool and happening atmosphere. The new style sashimi is to die for. Try also the grilled eggplant, Scampi Tempura, and Nigiri Sushi set.
Cool place for excellent breakfast. Try the Truffle Scrambled Egg, the Eggs Benedict or just a Fry Up of Bacon, Mushrooms & Tomatoes. Coffee is great too.
Kylie Kwong uses nothing but the best seasonal organic ingredients in all dishes. Try Fried Eggs with chilli and XO sauce, Steamed Rice Noodles with Braised Wagyu, Crispy Duck with Blood Plums.

The quality of food here has taken a nose dive! Totally atrocious. Xiao Long Pao that's totally dry, noodles as salty as the Dead Sea, Vegetables from the Old Folks Home, microwaved Cheong Fun. Avoid!

Known formerly as "Hock Chew Chicken Rice" before they shifted to this premise, its simple unpretentious good old fashioned chicken rice with steamed & roasted chicken options. Try the pork balls too.

formattedAddress: No 11 Jalan 20/14 (same row as O&S) (Taman Paramount)

tip.text: Reputed as the best Teochew restaurant chain in HK, this K11 outlet sure didn't disappoint. The Teochew Cold Crab will send you to heaven, while the Whelk Broccoli and Oyster Porridge are winners.

venue.name: Pak Loh Chiu Chow Restaurant 百樂潮州鮑魚飯店

tip.text: With nice ambience and ever friendly staff to boot, the quality of food is ok, but can be better. However the small selection of cakes and sweets available are divine. I'll definitely return for more.

Opened by a supplier of high quality seafood to top restaurants in KL, this is the place where the freshness of the ingredients speak for themselves! Go for the salt baked salmon, lobsters, & Sashimi.

location.neighborhood: Mont Kiara, Kuala Lumpur, Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Delightful 2 Michelin Star establishment, specializing in classic Cantonese Cuisine given a new fresh interpretation. Must try includes Crispy Salted Chicken & Stir Fried Lobster w Shallots & Onions.
With 2 Michelin Stars awarded and ranked in the top 100 restaurants in the world, Amber oozes class and perfectly executed cuisine. Try the Hokkaido Sea Urchin and Girolles with Taiyouran Egg.

formattedAddress: The Landmark Mandarin Oriental, 15 Queen’s Rd C
location.address: The Landmark Mandarin Oriental, 15 Queen’s Rd C

contact.facebookName: Amber at The Landmark Mandarin Oriental, Hong Kong

tip.text: Divine 9 course tasting menu from Chef Konishi. Every dish was a winner, and the most spectacular being the Grilled Kagoshima Wagyu Beef and the French Pigeon and Foie Gras En Croute. A must try.

location.address: Shop 1, G/F, The Oakhill, 16 Wood Rd
formattedAddress: Shop 1, G/F, The Oakhill, 16 Wood Rd

tip.text: Well deserved 2 Michelin Star rated establishment. Excellent food, ambience & view to boot. Try the Baked Turbot, Grilled King Crab Leg, Aged Sirloin, Fried Zucchini, Beef Tartare, & Croquette.
"Smushis" are mini opened face sandwiches. Out of the 6 options, the smoked salmon and shellfish are the best. The Tenderloin Steak Sandwich is also yummy. Please don't leave before trying the cakes.
Excellent Japanese outlet with a French twist. Winner of the 2013 World Sushi Championship in Tokyo n deservedly so. The Kobe beef and duck breast are TDF. Get the Chef's Omakase set.
Very good French Bistro near Nyhavn. All the dishes ordered were right up there. Start with freshly shucked oysters, on to Steak Tartare/Grilled Lobster (that's heavenly) & end with Profiteroles.
The food is awesome but service falls flat on the face! Fish Balls, Lobster Pot Rice, Hand Pulled Chicken are all out of this world..that is if you ever get served at all! Pokerfaced captain 👎🏼👎🏼!
Excellent authentic Shanghainese dishes. Must try includes 8 Treasure Duck Stuffed with Glutinous Rice, Stewed Pork Knuckle, Scallion Noodles, Pork Belly w Garlic Sauce & Grilled Fish with Scallion.

formattedAddress: 建国路328号｜328 Jianguo West Rd. (Xiangyang Road)
location.address: 建国路328号｜328 Jianguo West Rd.

tip.text: You get great breakfast and brunch here. Order a few of the tapas sized dishes or sets to share out. Try the Pork Burger with Foie Gras, Iberico Ham Toasties & Angus grilled beef. Lovely courtyard.

Small restaurant with only 7 tables, serving excellent authentic Shanghainese Cuisine. Try the Crab Roe Rice Noodle, Baked Fish with Scallions, Stewed Pork Belly with Man Dou, and Red Lantern Chicken.

location.crossStreet: M. Huaihai Rd. | 淮海中路
formattedAddress: 41 Tianping Rd. | 天平路41号 (M. Huaihai Rd. | 淮海中路)

tip.text: Inspired by Hakkasan, the chef gives new twists to Chinese Cuisine, conjuring up innovative, unique & delicious dishes. Try Soon Hock Wallet, Braised Wagyu Cheek, Ruyi Sushi & Winter Melon Noodle.
Opened by the same guys behind Artisans Coffee, you're assured of great coffee, brewed just the right way. Great ambience too.

formattedAddress: C22, Concourse Floor, Atria Shopping Gallery (Jalan SS 22/23, Damansara Jaya)
location.address: C22, Concourse Floor, Atria Shopping Gallery

venue.name: Artistry By Artisan Coffee Bars Sdn Bhd

tip.text: Overhyped cafe serving pastries and breakfast. Cool ambience but food can be improved. Egg Benedict is fair, and Chilling Cheese Toast is unique. Texture of croissant is too heavy. Coffee is fair
Very good seafood restaurant. The baked Sabah Flower Crab in superior stock, steamed Soon Hock, and Black Pepper King Crab Tung Hoon are great. End with Coconut Almond Milk.
Lef by Master Chef Hideaki Oritsuki, formerly of Sushi Hinata, sashimi and sushis are fresh, succulent, delectable and perfectly executed by Ori-San. Try the Omakase @ RM480++ for a great experience.

location.address: Vipod Residences (Block C-1), Jalan Kia Peng
formattedAddress: Vipod Residences (Block C-1), Jalan Kia Peng

tip.text: Delightful restaurant with great ambience and attentive service. Food was great too. The Roasted Rack of Lamb was perfectly done. Dutch White Asparagus and Grilled Black Angus Beef were great too.
Daorae Plus is the higher end of the Daorae chain of restaurants. Expect better choices of dishes. Barbecue beef ribs, Spicy Noodle Kimchi Salad, and the Pork Rib Soup are noteworthy.
One of the best Chicken Rice around. The Roast Chicken is tender and served fresh piping hot, with crispy fragrant skin. Do try the Char Siew, which is to die for. Expect to queue.
Smooth coconut ice cream with coconut flesh served in a coconut shell. All 4 scoops of it but I guarantee that you will scoff it down like lightning! Try the coconut juice too. Highly recommended.
This is the outlet helmed by the former chef of CocoTei. Sashimi, especially Otoro and Hamachi, are fresh and succulent. Try the Foie Gras Chawanmushi and Teppanyaki Wagyu. Temaki are also great.
Definitely the best newcomer in the restaurant scene. Chef Darren Teoh conjures up 10 and 5 course menus that showcase creative interplay of flavors, presenting dishes that are perfectly executed.
Nice ambience and great Shabu Shabu offerings. Go for the Kobe Beef set which comes with two Hairy Crab dishes too.

location.crossStreet: ティファニー銀座ビル
formattedAddress: 銀座2-7-17 (ティファニー銀座ビル)

tip.text: Simple inexpensive shop selling Kyushu Ramen. Great tasting pork broth with four variants. Go for the original pork tonkotsu broth and the Kabonan spicy option.

venue.name: Kyushu Jangara (九州じゃんがら 銀座店)

tip.text: 2 Michelin Star establishment, with great service, friendly atmosphere, great entertaining sushi chef, with world class delicate, exquisite and perfectly executed sushi and sashimi. Try the omakase.

formattedAddress: 銀座8-10-3 (銀座三鈴ビル B1F)

venue.name: Sushi Kanesaka (鮨かねさか 銀座本店)

tip.text: Daiwa is one of the best, if not, the best sushi outlet in Tsukiji Market. Be prepared to queue for ages, and dine in cramped spaces, but you'll get the freshest, sweet and delectable morsels ever!
High on 40th Floor of The Heron, you're ensured the best bird's eye view of London, while sampling great British cuisine. Duck & Waffle, Grilled Octopus, Eggs en Cocotte, Foie Gras Creme Brûlée are 👍
Exquisite, innovative, classy and avantgarde cuisine, coupled with great ambience and service. Wasabi Prawns, Braised Abalone w Truffles, Poached Eggs and Durian Vanilla Soufflé are to die for!
Lovely cafe located in the heart of Soho. Serves excellent coffee that's robust, strong, fragrant and brewed at the perfect temperature. Great and friendly service from the staff too.

NYC based French bistro style restaurant, with great ambience, good food and friendly service. French Onion Soup, Steak Au Pouvre, Sole Meunière all good. The bomb? Raspberry Soufflé! Don't miss that!

Great ambience, great food with excellent service. Go for the "new style" dishes rather than the traditional ones. Hamachi and Suzuki sashimi, Spicy baked Crab, Lobster Tempura, Lamb Cutlets are good.
Hip, chic & stylish ambience, with food that matches all the hype lavished on this place. Peking Duck w Caviar, Baked Royal King Crab, Scallop & Prawn Cakes, Salted Beggar Chicken 👍🏼. Book ahead!
Great coffee that's flavorful, strong and brewed at the correct temperature. Try the blueberry poppy seed cake too. Sandwiches are also great.

Excellent high tea selection served in a charming room at the Gallery, with an extensive list of teas to choose from. Scones were crisped on the outside soft on the inside, cakes & sandwiches spot on.
The Irish Beef Belly and the Flat Iron Steak are very very good!! Done to perfection, the steaks are very juicy and flavorful. Definitely worth a check out!
One Michelin star establishment serving excellent dim sum ala carte dishes. Practically everything is great on the menu. Try the divine Venison Puff, Pan Fried Turnip Cake & Jasmine Smoked Pork Ribs.
Excellent place for traditional fish and chips in Covent Garden, with a beer batter that's nicely crisped. Choose from options of Sole, Halibut, Plaice, Dory or Flake. Great calamari too.

There's only 3 items on a non existent menu. Beef Burger with Cheese and Bacon, GrilledSteamed Lobster and Lobster Roll. My pick is the Lobster Roll which is divine. Burger & grilled lobster also good
One of the best Chinese restaurant in London, with nice ambience (for a change). Dim sum and ala carte dishes are excellent. Don't miss Lobster Noodles, Crispy Duck Pancakes, Wasabi Prawn Dumplings.
One of the oldest and most renowned restaurants in Wien, you can't get much better for Austrian fare given that modern twist, with great service and ambience too. Highly recommended.
An "institution" in Vienna, with clientele including Schubert, you get great traditional Austrian fare here. Veal Schnitzel, Beef Goulash, Meatloafs & Hazelnut Soufflé w Chocolate Sauce are superb!
Located in St Peter's Abbey, ambience is way cooler than cool, with excellent service and food to boot too. Try Coq Au Vin, Saddle of Pork, Fillet of Hereford Beef and end with Salzburger Knockerl!

location.neighborhood: Neben Dom, direkt neben Kirche zu St.Peter

tip.text: Set inside a quaint "alley way" in old Salzburg, this place serves very good cakes and coffee or hot chocolate. Hot dishes may pale in comparison though.
Ultra chic ambience coupled with great service and excellent food. Not only finger foods are great, the ala carte dishes are also excellent. Worth giving it a try.
Excellent place for a slice of cake and pastries and a cup of coffee or tea. All their cakes are yummy. You can even see how the cakes are prepared from the open kitchen. Be prepared to queue.
This place serves great traditional Austrian cuisine. Good ambience and service is commendable. Try the Wiener Schnitzel, Fried Chicken, Boiled Beef with Root Vegetables and Beef Goulash.
This is the home of the famous Pork Schnitzel, which comes in the size of a dinner plate. Giant, juicy but tender slices of pork crumbed to perfection. Mix Salad and fried potatoes are awesome too!

Forget about this place if you're into ambience. Great food? You're spot on. Excellent Sang Har Mee, Steamed Village Chicken, Lap Mei Fan, Curry Wild Boar & Crispy Shell Crab. Order Coconut juice too.

venue.name: Restauran Tian Tian Lai Seafood (天天来海鲜饭店)

tip.text: Newly crowned No. 1 Restaurant in Asia, this is molecular cuisine at its best. Innovative, unique, executed precision, but most of all, ultra delicious, all dishes are beyond outstanding! A must have.

location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร
formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10330

tip.text: One of the most revered & premier Thai restaurants in Bangkok, you can expect delicate flavors exquisitely prepared dishes here. Green Curry Wagyu Beef, Steamed Trout, & Grilled Pork Cheek standout.

location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร
formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10120

tip.text: "There's always room for desserts", says the logo, and I definitely agree! The signature Shibuya Honey Toasts is heavenly, so is the Nutella Toasts. Add bananas to it for added zing.

location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร
formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10330

venue.name: After You (อาฟเตอร์ ยู)

tip.text: They serve some of best tasting beef noodles in Bangkok, or anywhere in the world. Go for the Wagyu or Kobe Beef with Slim Noodles. Slurp up the broth. Fish balls and Grilled Pork Rice are great too.

location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร
formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10330

venue.name: NUER KOO (เนื้อคู่)

tip.text: The world's most expensive chicken rice is still the best chicken rice in the world. The rice is still as fragrant as ever and the steamed chicken as smooth as silk. The beef hor fun worth a try too!

formattedAddress: Level 5, Mandarin Orchard Singapore (333 Orchard Rd.)

tip.text: Great place for brunch or Al fresco dining/meal. Eggs Benedict/Royale is excellent so is the Jones Big Breakfast and Bacon Roll. Try the Jones Wagyu Burger too.
One of the finest Japanese restaurants in Sgp, you can expect nothing but well executed dishes here. The signature Sliced Beef with Truffle on Rice, Bara Chirashi, & Truffles on White Fish are tops!
Go and grab the Indon Ayam Panggang set. Comes served with rice and omelette. Yummy to the max. The Chicken Curry or Ikan Panggang sets are also superb! Highly recommended.

formattedAddress: #B4-04G, Food Opera @ ION Orchard (2 Orchard Turn)

tip.text: Forget about the ambience. Reasonably priced (bordering on cheap), generally great tasting dishes, what's there not to like? Lala Beehoon, Steamed Chicken w wine, Butter Prawns & Guiness Ribs are 👍.

venue.name: Restaurant Wong Poh 旺来海鲜饭店

tip.text: Helmed by Chef Korn of Erawan, they churn out excellent classic Thai dishes here. Try Fireball for starter, then continue with the great Kao Moo, Seafood Tom Yam, Roast Pork Kailan, & Ice cream.
They serve some of the best seafood dishes around. Alaskan Crab, steamed with eggs, and fried with butter sauce are clear winners. The mega sized steamed Soon Hock & Lobster Noodles 👍👍. Go try.

formattedAddress: 8 Jalan 11/116B Kuchai Entrepreneurs Park (Kuchai Entrepreneurs Park)

tip.text: Get a table at the Courtyard at the back of the cafe. Very nice... And it's shaded too!! Downside, food and coffee nothing to shout about. Stick to staples of ham bacon & sunny side up for breakfast.

Azuma consistently churns out great Japanese staples. Sashimi/sushi are always fresh and succulent. Baked Scampi with Mayonaise, Ebi Tempura & Terriyaki Chicken are superb. Avoid Steak with miso sauce
Great ambience and great food, Neil Perry's outlet lives up to its reputation as one of the leading restaurants in Sydney. Alaskan Crab Avocado Salad, Lobster Thermidor, and Wagyu Steaks are good!
Famous joint serving arguably the best ribs in Sydney. Tender "meat falling of the bone" pork ribs, done to perfection. The Mussels, with White Wine and Cream & Caesar Salad with Anchovies are great!

formattedAddress: 130 Roscoe St (btwn Campbell Pde & Gould St)

tip.text: Chef Chase Kojima deserves every single accolade bestowed on him. Dishes are exquisite, innovative and totally refreshing. Try the "new" style sashimi and sushi rolls. Robata dishes are also strong.

formattedAddress: Level G, The Darling (80 Pyrmont St.)

tip.text: Bill Granger's original outlet serving Sydney's best breakfast of smooth as silk scrambled eggs and ricotta hot cakes. Prices are steep, but this is the one to beat. Love the community table too!
If you're after fresh oysters, and seafood dishes, you can get others with same offerings at 1/2 the price. But dining with the Sydney Harbour Bridge, Opera House and the sea for company, this is it!
Excellent food. Roast Duck, XO Sauce Pippies, Crabmeat Fried Rice with roe are all good. Dim Sums are gems too. Scallop Prawn Shumai, Abalone/Chicken Glutinous Rice, Prawn Toasts w Foie Gras all 👍
Ranked in the Top 500 restaurants of Asia by Miele's, Erawan prides serves Royal Thai Cuisine. Dishes are exquisitely superb. Red Curry Alaskan Crab, Lily Petal Snacks, Lamb Cutlet curry standout.

location.address: 22-1, Jalan PJU 5/16, Dataran Sunway, Kota Damansara
formattedAddress: 22-1, Jalan PJU 5/16, Dataran Sunway, Kota Damansara

tip.text: Pretty dessert outlet with cute interior. Try Le Cempedak, where waffles are made with Cempedak, dunked in Cempedak sauce and served with Vanilla. Churros are excellent too.
This outlet is opened by the former chef of Mizu@BV1. Superb cuisine made with really fresh ingredients. Sashimi, Foie Gras Maki, Wagyu teppanyaki, Yellowtail Shioyaki, Ebi Tempura n Chawanmushi 👍👍
The cafe with one of the most celebrated openings in recent years, definitely lived up to all the hype, rewarding you with robust strong and smooth coffee. Check out their specialty beans for tastes.
This eagerly awaited restaurant is now opened. Choice of 4/5 course menus, using the freshest ingredients around. Dishes prepared exquisitely with great interplay of flavors. Prices r reasonable. 👍👍

formattedAddress: No.44 Persiaran Zaaba (Taman Tun Dr Ismail)

tip.text: I scream, you scream, we all scream for Durian or Cempedak Ice Cream! Rich, decadent, smooth, fragrant and yummy Durian and/or Cempedak Ice Cream that go very well with their crispy waffles. Try both!
Excellent Spanish cuisine, served in great quiet ambience. Squid Ink Paella, Scallops with Caviar, Spicy Prawns Aglio Olio Pasta are all superb. Pre order the Lamb Shank, which is the bomb!!

Famous outlet serving all types of live seafood, cooked to your order, with a wide range of fish, clams, crustaceans and geoduck to choose from. Dishes are good but I've tasted better. Overpriced too.
Forget about ambience and service. If you're after seriously good chicken rice, go no further. Their smooth tender steamed chicken served with fragrant rice nails it. Curry Pork Ribs are super too!
New seafood restaurant in unlikely location of Park 51 at 222 area. Food is very fresh n good. Try the Steamed Snow Crab with egg, Hakka Tofu, Suckling Piglet, and the Signature Baked Rice.

venue.name: Star Light Seafood Naturalle 星光海鲜庆丰楼

tip.text: The famous pork ribs from Bali has opened in KL, with other local dishes incorporated. Signature BBQ pork ribs are great. Try the Babi Guling, and Bah Kut Soup. Finish with the Fried Pisang Bacon.

formattedAddress: 2, Jalan 20/70A, Desa Sri Hartamas (Jalan Sri Hartamas 22)

tip.text: Utterly horrible and inedible. Ordered the Cantonese Kuey Teow and Mee Mamak and both contained tons of NaCl!!! Must have used sea water as stock!! Not tempted to give them another try at all.
Great new restaurant managed by Rowley Leigh. Excellent ambience and service. Food is also great. Try the Wagyu Onglet with truffle gravy, and the Steamed Garoupa with Ceps and Persillade.

location.neighborhood: Admiralty, Central and Western District, Hong Kong

tip.text: Famed outlet specializing in Beef Brisket/Beef noodles. Choice of Yee Mee, thick noodle in Traditional broth or Curry sauce. Traditional broth is excellent. Be prepared to queue.

Excellent cuisine, great ambience and service. Try their signature Roast Pigeon with Osmanthus and Winter Melon Soup. Dim Sums are excellent too. Siew Mai, Steamed Turnip Cake n Custard Buns are tops.

venue.name: Spring Moon 嘉麟閣 (嘉麟樓)

tip.text: With 2 Michelin Stars under their belt, this place serves simple but more than excellent "home cooked" style dishes, which emphasizes on the freshness of ingredients. All their dishes are commendable!

location.address: 1/F, Lan Kwai Fong Hotel, 3 Kau U Fong
formattedAddress: 1/F, Lan Kwai Fong Hotel, 3 Kau U Fong

tip.text: The steaks and appetizers are very good here. Although we didn't get the US Tomahawk, the U.S. Prime 120 days Wet-aged T-Bone was super n so was the Melba Toasts with Mushrooms and melted Camembert!

location.address: 3-4/F, The L Place, 139 Queen's Rd C
formattedAddress: 3-4/F, The L Place, 139 Queen's Rd C

tip.text: They serve one of the best coffees in HK, without a doubt. Coffee is robust and heavenly strong. Try their cakes too. The Choc Fudge and Lemon Poppyseed are good.

location.address: Shop 3023, 3/F, IFC Mall, 1 Harbour View St
formattedAddress: Shop 3023, 3/F, IFC Mall, 1 Harbour View St

tip.text: Forget about Yung Kee. This is the real deal for HK Roast Goose. Their "25 steps" goose is crispy on the outside, succulent on the inside, tastes divine n costs less! Try the Crispy Roast Pork too!

venue.name: Yat Lok Restaurant 一樂燒鵝 (一樂燒鵝)

tip.text: One of the best breakfast buffet spots around. The spread is amazing, and the quality of the dishes are great too. Downside is the price can be steep, but that's expected from this establishment.

formattedAddress: 7/F, Island Shangri-La Hong Kong, Pacific Place, 88 Queensway (at Supreme Court Rd)
location.address: 7/F, Island Shangri-La Hong Kong, Pacific Place, 88 Queensway

tip.text: Serves one of the best local good old wonton noodles, with options of Char Cheong, Beef Brisket, or Spicy Dried Shrimps. The Prawn Wonton Soup Noodles, Crab Porridge, Fish Balls and Fried Wonton r 👍

Ranked No. 3 in the world during its peak, RyuGin is still a force to be reckoned with. All dishes are delicately executed and presentation is tops. Try the Chef's Degustation Menu. Excellent sampling

formattedAddress: 六本木7-17-24 (サイド六本木ビル 1F)

tip.text: Great tempura with a wide array of choices from this 1 Michelin Star establishment. Ten-Ichi boasts out of the norm choices like Sea Cucumber tempura, Sea Eel with Bone and Onions. Try the chef set.
This cafe on the 6th Floor of Matsuya Ginza, serves nice coffee, tea and a good selection of cakes. However, the best item there is undoubtedly the Caramel Custard Pudding, which is the best ever!

formattedAddress: 中央区銀座3-6-1, 東京都

tip.text: With 3 generations of expertise, 3 Michelin Stars Kyoboshi has been rated the top tempura restaurant in the world. Only superlative praises can do justice here. Tempura steak perfectly done? Must try!

formattedAddress: 銀座5-5-9 (オージオ銀座ビル 6F)

tip.text: Sushi Kanaseka is awarded 2 Michelin Stars for a few years running. As expected, ingredients are extremely fresh and the sushi/sashimi dishes are exquisitely delectable. Try the Omakase for sampling.

One of the top places for "Dip Ramen" in Tokyo, be ready to queue for 1 hour. Ramen is firm n springy, dip sauce ultra flavorful from hours of stewing of pork ribs, bonito flakes & miso. Go for spicy.

location.crossStreet: 東京駅一番街 B1F 東京ラーメンストリート
formattedAddress: 丸の内1-9-1 (東京駅一番街 B1F 東京ラーメンストリート)

tip.text: Very fresh and good sushi here. Rated as one of the top sushi places in Tokyo, every morsel served doesn't disappoint. Try the Chef Recommendation sushi Omakase set.
Only superlatives can describe the superb Teppanyaki inspired dishes here. The Steamed Abalone flavored with Black Truffle, Scallop with Cream Sauce, Queen Crab & White Truffle Risotto are all TDF 👍!

venue.name: Ginza Ukai-tei (銀座 うかい亭)

tip.text: Great cafe serving noodles and simple dishes from Nagasaki. Noodles were great with simple yet flavorful broth.
Ningyocho Imahan Ginza is one of the top Sukiyaki specialist in Tokyo. The sukiyaki and steak courses are out of this world. Go for the special beef, especially the champion for the year. 👍👍👍

formattedAddress: 銀座6-8-7 (交詢ビルディング 5F)

venue.name: Ningyocho Imahan (人形町今半 銀座店)

tip.text: With 7 generations of expertise on Inawiwa Udon, wyou're guaranteed a gastronomic experience here. The noodles is as smooth & silky as a baby's bottom. The tamago and Oyakodon are also tops. Superb!

venue.name: Ginza Sato Yosuke (銀座 佐藤養助)

tip.text: Surprisingly this place serves some of the best tasting dishes for a buffet. The choices may not be that extensive but the quality of the dishes are definitely commendable. Worth a try.

formattedAddress: Traders Hotel, Kuala Lumpur (Kuala Lumpur City Centre)

tip.text: This place serves some of the best aged steaks around in KL. Wide choice of cuts prepared exactly the way you requested. The Wagyu Ribeye, Tenderloin and Porterhouse stand out. Stay clear from T Bone.
At RM29 per pop, it's hard pressed to justify the price tag of "Not Your Ordinary" Chicken Rice. Chicken is smooth tender and the rice is fragrant. The Cottage Pie and Chicken Chop are good too.
One of the best restaurants for Teochew Cuisine. Try the Baked Lobster with Garlic, Teochew Roast Suckling Pig, Crispy Skin Sea Cucumber, Cold Crab, and Braised Goose Fillet. Move over Crystal Jade!!

formattedAddress: #01-02, Chui Huay Lim Club (190 Keng Lee Rd.)

tip.text: Widest selection of teas to accompany your meal. Food is great. Dim sum is more than respectable. Try the Peking Duck, Braised Pork Ribs with Breadsticks, Baked Cod w Glutinous Rice n Wasabi Prawns.
Organic milk ice cream from Korea with choice of toppings. The ice cream is light, smooth and not overly sweet. Try the honey comb or liquid honey topping. Perfect combination. Down side? Expensive!
Pork dishes, especially local ones are great. Pork Satay, Crispy Roast a Pork, Hokkien Mee, Bah Kut Teh, Scallops with Bacon, BBQ Pork Ribs n Pork Knuckle are all 👍👍. Good choice of wines/whiskey.
Great selection of gelato. However, the biggest surprise is their soft vanilla affogato. It may be void of liqueur, but it's surprising yummy. Try it!!

location.address: Lot GK, Ground Floor, Bangsar Shopping Centre
formattedAddress: Lot GK, Ground Floor, Bangsar Shopping Centre

tip.text: They introduced further new menus. Try the roast pork with wasabi soy and the spicy mince pork tacos. But give the hot plate rice a miss.

location.address: Lot G110 Ground Floor, Bangsar Shopping Centre
formattedAddress: Lot G110 Ground Floor, Bangsar Shopping Centre

tip.text: Great traditional & modern Indonesian/Balinese fare. Great ambience and service too. Try the Sumatran Beef Pao, Pork Belly Popia, Barramundi with Swimmer Crab, Bebek Rendang and Suckling Pig.
They roast 100% Indonesian coffees beans here with a wide selection of choices. It's definitely one of the best coffee outlets in Bali. Highly recommended.
Great place for breakfast. Their grilled leg ham is very good. Eggs Benedict is to die for. Also try The Full, consisting of samples of all their breakfast items. Coffees are good too.
Excellent French Fusion Cuisine with great views of padi fields. Try their Pan Seared Foie Gras, Lobster Ravioli, 14 hours Crispy a Pork Belly and any of their primary cut steaks. End with a soufflé!
Serves one of the more respectable coffees around. Espressos, Capuccino and Flat White reasonable. The best is their Green Hornet. Excellent thirst quencher. Throw in 2 shots of vodka for kick!!
The reputation Naughty Nuri's has for its famous pork ribs is not unfounded. Ribs that's juicy, soft, tender, and with the meat falling off the bone, this is as close to pig's heaven you can get.
Superb Aussie outlet for breakfast brunch and lunch with great selection of choices. Try the Pulled Pork Charcoal Roll, Thai 18 Hours Pork Belly on Glass Noodles, washed down with Fruit Salad! Nice!
Excellent Indonesian cuisine with a slight Aussie twist. Try the Signature Pork Belly, the heavenly Crab Dumpling Bisque & stewed Panang lamb curry, eaten with butter naan. End with Kampung Snickers!
Super ambience, excellent views and great food. Try the Lobster with Inawiwa Noodles, New Style Scallop Sashimi, Yellowtail Sashimi with Jalapeño, Tuna Taco & King Crab Tempura. Prepare to pay!

Microscopic serves of Thai noodles with choices of beef/chicken in spicy, non-spicy, and vinegar sauces. One mouthful per serve at RM1.90 per pop. Yummy? So so. Ambience? Nope. Service? Bad. Go figure

formattedAddress: Publika (Lot G3.30a, Block C5), Jalan Dutamas 1
location.address: Publika (Lot G3.30a, Block C5), Jalan Dutamas 1

tip.text: This place continues to churn out unbelievable twists to staple M'sian and Western cuisine. The new Pasta Carbonara with Marmite Chicken, and the Durian Crepe with Ice Cream are very very good!!
Excellent restaurant with excellent service! Oysters are freshly shucked, the Wagyu ribeye & Angus sirloin were done exactly at medium rare. Try Vanilla Creme Brûlée n Coffee Ice Cream as finale. 👍👍
Excellent asian fusion restaurant. Wagyu Pot Sticker and Chicken Spare Ribs for appetizers, and the Red Duck Leg Curry accompanied by creamy coconut rice, are 👍. Cocktails mean too. Try Thai Moon.
Set amidst an alley way, this cafe serves great coffee. The Short Macchiato is on the dot. The Eggs Benedict with Bacon is heavenly. Beware of the grouchy proprietor who can be crude sometimes!
Forget about the ambience, or fine dining finesse. If you want excellent HK style roast duck, soya sauce chicken, roast pork or generally good affordable no frills HK food, look no further.
Smooth fragrant coffee served at the perfect temperature. Their ice coffee with ice cream is to die for!! They serve a decent array of tapas after 3 pm. Still serve one of the best coffees around!
Fragrant coffee/latte/Capuccino, brewed exactly at the correct temperature. Only downside is it tends to be too weak for my liking. Ask for added shot of coffee for that much needed kick.
3rd time here and still as awesome!Fresh as ever Petite Claire Oysters and Ahi Tuna Salad, excellent Foie Gras terrine, succulent n tender Beef Short Rib, divine Madeleines. What's there not to like!

formattedAddress: 45 Flinders Ln. (btwn Exhibition St. & Spring St.)

tip.text: It's all superb from Fritto Misto, to Gnocchi w Suckling Pig Sausages n Garlic, Black Ink Spagetti w Blue Swimmer Crab n Tomatoes, to mains of Lamb Cutlets and Roasted Veal, n to Doughnuts w Nutella!!

Great restaurant by Mark Best of Sydney. Try sinful starters of Sea Urchin + Potato "Sandwich", Gruyere Cheese Soufle, and mains of Wood Grilled Blackmore Wagyu 9 with Chuck Ribs. Breakfast great too!
Great ambience and service. Miso Cod, New Style Sashimi, Wagyu Steak with 3 sauces, scallops, Braised Pork Belly are fresh & great. Signature Masterchef Sushis and Maki are let down. Trio of Mochis 👍
Noisy and bustling, this place serves up some of the best Oz Asian fusion food around. Try the Caramelized Pork, beef short rib with nam pla, braised wagyu with rice roll, and Palm sugar sundae. 👍👍
The menu at Ippudo @ BSC is different from other outlets. There's 11 additional items on offer, and they are good. Try the Ippudo Kuro, the Misoshiromaru Ramen and the Pork Rib. 👍

location.address: Lot G110 Ground Floor, Bangsar Shopping Centre
formattedAddress: Lot G110 Ground Floor, Bangsar Shopping Centre

tip.text: Set amidst cosy colonial ambience, you can dine on dishes of an era bygone. Try the Hainanese Chicken Rice Balls, Inche Kabin, Mulligatawny Soup, and English Trifle. There's a jazz band at night too!
Colombian outlet offering good strong coffees made from a wide choice of beans and different brewing methods. Try the "tasting menu" to sample the diversity of flavors. One of the best in K Lumpur. 👍
Melt-in-your-mouth Fatty Tuna Belly, exquisite assortment of Sushi, punctuated by Foie Gras and caviar, succulent sashimi, perfectly seared Wagyu fillet..this is heaven. Go for Chef's Omakase. Enjoy!
Nice ambience with Yemeni flavored decor and lots of memorabilia on display. Coffee is on the weak side and temperature is a wee bit too high, resulting in loss of flavor. Will try the food menu.

formattedAddress: 15, Lorong Rahim Kajai 13 (Taman Tun Dr. Ismail)

tip.text: This is part of the chain, reputed to serve the best Teochew cuisine in HK. Have the braised soya goose, oyster omelette, fish/crab cakes, pan fried superior soy pomfret together with porridge. Great!
Seafood Chowder means canned mushroom soup with bits of non-fresh prawns, mussels thrown in. Steaks are greasy and tastes of pepper and Lea Perrin Sauce. Go for it if you like your arteries blocked!
Yet ano one of the better cafés cropping up in TTDI. Great coffee although slightly on the weak side. Ask for extra shot if you like yours strong. Try out the Eggs Benedict and Steak Sandwich too.
This has to be the hidden of all cafés in KL. Coffee is strong and velvety. Churros is easily the best in KL. The snacks are also great. Try the Shepherd's Pie and Chicken Wrap. Super like.
Gorgeous place for late morning breakfast, or breakfast whatsoever!! Best ever bacon square pizza, and sausage rolls, fresh yoghurt and fruits. Serves great caffe machiato too!
The best paella I've ever tasted! Hands down. Try the Lobster and Shellfish Paella and Rice with Crayfish and clams. Excellent. For starters order the grilled calamari and razor clams.
The best creative tapas I ever had. From anchovy fillets on tomato bruschetta, gamba with rice right through to cannelloni stuffed with truffles, gambas ravioli....they all will send you to heaven.
Great breakfast. The bacon is excellent. The club sandwich is out of this world. Only problem is the service. The waitress looks like she hasn't woken up yet. Slumber service!!!
Cool place with a view to die for!!! Nibbling on tapas with the architectural splendor of Barcelona for company? Now that's unbeatable!
Excellent cuisine!!! The Greenhouse Tomatoes with Wasabi Sesame Sauce, Spicy Lobster with Korean Glass Noodles, Pan Seared Scallops with Foie Gras Ragout, Garoupa with Pomelo Salad, are must tries.
The pan roasted Flounder and pumpkin salad are out of this world. So is the Foie Gras parfait with Toasted Brioche.

formattedAddress: 45 Flinders Ln. (btwn Exhibition St. & Spring St.)

tip.text: Excellent breakfast here! Everything on the menu looks tempting! Highly recommended.

venue.name: Pao Xiang Bak Kut Teh (宝香绑线肉骨茶)
